    "body": "Have you tried a local install of Mathjax ? From the link you provided, it seem like the `firefox-and-localfont` link only apply to pages loaded with `file://` which we don't do as you are most probably served through localhost. \n\nWe might be able to ship font or provide a simple way to install, the problem is I don't see any way to configure mathjax CDN to use font hosted on localhost. So it will basically not help at all when people came across this bug.\n\nIf we need to depend on `mathjax-fonts-extras` in some cases this is maybe something that should be dealt with by packagers (might be worth pinging juliantaylor about that later on).\n"
  },
