    "body": "Hi, I'm part of the MathJax team and just wanted to say hi in case we can help out with any questions.  It was a bit hard for me to judge the situation in the discussion on our user group -- my iPython knowledge is too limited. I'm not sure what the problem is if you're using a local webserver, actually.\n\nI agree that this is probably more of a packaging/dependency question. Installing STIX or our MathJax fonts locally seems like the best option as it helps elsewhere as well (like on MathML site that don't use MathJax). The debian `mathjax-fonts` package is probably better than the `mathjax-fonts-extras` one -- the former has otf and woff fonts. There's also a stix-fonts package IIRC; the STIX fonts are more complete when it comes to the more obscure unicode points.\n"
  },
