    "body": "@pkra: The packages are fine -- On my Kubuntu Raring system (and in upstream Debian) the ipython(3)-notebook packages depends on ipython-notebook-common which depends on libjs-mathjax. As I said, the problem caused here is because of Firefox's strict interpretation of the common origin policy. \n\nIPython apparently doesn't provide the OTF fonts in whatever location the page is loaded from so Fx doesn't display them. It would seem that if IPy relies on MathJax then the pages generated by IPy Notebook should explicitly declare the origin of the fonts as safe or something like that -- I'm really not sure about how this common origin policy is to be utilized by webpages or is it by webservers.\n\nAs I also said, installing the STIX outline fonts to my system doesn't help any in solving this problem. All I know is that without the MathJax PNG fonts installed I don't get any Math display from MathJax within IPy Notebook.\n\nMaybe you people want to bring in Mozilla people so they can explain what the technical problem is and how you should solve it. I am only a user of all three software involved -- IPy, MathJax and Fx -- I know almost nothing about the technicalities.\n"
  },
