    "created_at": "2013-07-03T04:39:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-07-03T04:39:01Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "But the local-files logic is for `file://`, not `localhost`, right? Those two are totally different entities.  This is why I am confused - MathJax served from a CDN, or from the local filesystem (either from the package, or from mathjax in my profile) does seem to work just fine with Firefox on my machines, and I would expect we would have heard about this much sooner if it were the general issue you describe.\n\nNote that, when mathjax is installed locally (it doesn't make any difference where on the filesystem), the notebook is served at\n\n```\nhttps://localhost:8888/u-u-i-d\n```\n\nand the mathjax fonts are served from\n\n```\nhttps://localhost:8888/static/mathjax/fonts/...\n```\n\nSo I cannot imagine that shipping mathjax with IPython would make any difference from having it anywhere else on the filesystem.\n"
  },
