    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> But the local-files logic is for `file://`, not `localhost`, right?\n\nYes and no, the security policy holds for both but the effects are different. `file://` treats everything that's not a subfolder as a different origin and blocks it (and since there's no server, there's no way to override this with CORS headers). A webserver can run into these, see [our docs on shared installations](http://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/installation.html#notes-about-shared-installations) but I don't see how`localhost` could run into this issue.\n\n> and the mathjax fonts are served from `https://localhost:8888/static/mathjax/fonts/...`\n> So I cannot imagine that shipping mathjax with IPython would make any difference from having it anywhere else on the filesystem.\n\nAgreed. That setup should not cause any issues. \n\n@jamadagni are you using `localhost` or `file://` to access your notebook?\n"
  },
