    "body": "Hmm -- sorry folks it would seem that it's a false alarm after all -- really sorry about all the fuss:\n\nI tried opening Fx in a clean profile and the error did not occur, and some testing back and forth and upon a hunch I turned on this option (which was off):\n\nEdit > Preferences > Content > Fonts > Advanced > Allow pages to select their own fonts instead of my selections above\n\n... and everything works fine without requiring any fonts-stix or fonts-mathjax-extras package to be installed. \n\nHowever I can't stand to see Arial on so many websites that seem to use it (probably via some silly web authoring tool that defaults to that font) so I can't enable the above just for IPy Notebook, so what I'll do is I'll just use Chromium for IPy Notebook (and for GitHub, where the commit etc icons appear as Tibetan characters!).\n\nI'm really sorry about causing all the fuss, but I did honestly think it was the problem with Fx's strict CO policy and so IPy should provide the workaround. Perhaps the MathJax people might add an FAQ to their site saying that if a Fx user finds the fonts are not displayed, they should try turning on the above setting.\n\nAgain, thank you both teams for IPy and MathJax!\n"
  },
